Stephane Le Foll, chief of staff to
French President-elect Francois Hollande, may become minister of
agriculture in a new government, Ouest France reported on its
website, without saying where it got the information.  Le Foll, 52, was elected to the European Parliament in 2004
and is a member of the group of socialists and democrats. He
sits on the parliamentâ€™s Committee on Agriculture and  Rural
Development , and in 2009 wrote a report on European Union
